{{Infobox school | name = | latin_name = | logo = AIU3color.jpg | image = | alt = | streetaddress = 475 East Waterfront Drive | city = Homestead | county = Allegheny County | state = [[Pennsylvania]] | zipcode = 15120 | type = Intermediate Unit | established = 1971 | information = Located at 420 sites throughout Allegheny County | website = http://www.aiu3.net 412-394-5700 }}The '''Allegheny Intermediate Unit''' (AIU) is a branch of the [[Pennsylvania Department of Education]], and is the largest of the 29 [[Intermediate Unit|intermediate unit]]s in [[Pennsylvania]]. It was created by the state’s [[Pennsylvania General Assembly|General Assembly]] in 1971, and is headquartered in [[Homestead, Pennsylvania|Homestead]].
The AIU provides specialized education services to 42 suburban public school districts and five career and technical centers in [[Allegheny County, Pennsylvania|Allegheny County]]. The agency, which has about 1,560 employees at 420 sites throughout the county, also operates 11 family centers and three schools for exceptional children. Funded by federal, state, county and private grants, the AIU coordinates more than 130 programs designed to help infants, young children, students and adults. In 2017, the programs offered by the AIU served 114,508 students in public schools.
== Leadership and Governance == [[File:AIU Headquarters.jpg|thumb|AIU Headquarters, Homestead, PA]] The AIU's Board of Directors has 13 members, elected from Allegheny County's 42 suburban public school districts. Dr. Linda B. Hippert has been the organization's executive director since 2008.
