{{Infobox building | name = Katuaq | native_name = | former_names = | alternate_names = Grønlands Kulturhus | image = Katuaq2008.JPG | alt = | caption = The undulating perimeter screen | map_type = | map_alt = | map_caption = | altitude = | building_type = | architectural_style = [[Modernism]] | structural_system = | cost = | client = Nuuk Municipality | owner = | current_tenants = | landlord = | location = | address = Imaneq 21 3900 Nuuk | location_town = [[Nuuk]] | location_country = [[Greenland]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|10|38|N|51|44|20|W|type:landamrk_region:GL|display=inline,title}} | start_date = 1994 | completion_date = 1997 | inauguration_date = February 15, 1997 | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | height = | diameter = | floor_count = | floor_area = 4800 square metres | main_contractor = | architect = [[Schmidt hammer lassen|Schmidt Hammer Lassen]] | architecture_firm = | structural_engineer = | services_engineer = | civil_engineer = | awards = | url = | references = }}
'''Katuaq''' ({{lang-da|Grønlands Kulturhus}}) is a [[cultural centre]] in [[Nuuk]], [[Greenland]].<ref>"[http://www.katuaq.gl/en/about_katuaq/welcome About Katuaq: Welcome]". Katuaq. Retrieved 2 January 2013.</ref> It is used for [[concert]]s, [[Art exhibition|exhibition]]s, conferences, and as a [[Film|cinema]]. Designed by [[Schmidt hammer lassen|Schmidt Hammer Lassen]], it was constructed as a joint project of the [[Greenland Home Rule Government]], the Nuuk Municipal Council and the [[Nordic Council of Ministers]] and was inaugurated on 15 February 1997.<ref>"[http://www.katuaq.gl/en/about_katuaq/the_building About Katuaq: The Building]". Katuaq. Retrieved 2 January 2013.</ref>
==Building== Katuaq is an L-shaped building with an undulating, backward-leaning screen facing onto Nuuk's central urban space. It is raised above the ground and clad in golden [[larch]] wood on both the inside and outside. The screen is inspired by the [[Aurora (astronomy)|northern lights]]. <ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.mimoa.eu/projects/Greenland/Nuuk/Katuaq%20Culture%20Centre|title=Katuaq Culture Centre|publisher=MIMOA|accessdate=23 June 2009}}</ref> This second skin also creates a contrast to the building proper. Between the perimeter screen and the core building lies the large [[foyer]] with three white freestanding elements in the shape of a triangle, square and circle.
==Facilities== Katuaq contains two [[auditorium|auditoria]], the larger one seating 1,008 people and the smaller one 508. The big auditorium is used for concerts, theatre, conferences, and as a cinema. Katuaq also provides meeting facilities, administrative offices and a café.
Offices: * [[The Nordic Institute in Greenland|NAPA - The Nordic Institute in Greenland]] * [[Hello Norden]], the [[Nordic Council of Ministers]] information service
[[Nuuk Center]], the country's first [[shopping mall]], is located right next door.
