{{Infobox language |name=Sauri |nativename= |region=[[Indonesia]]n [[Papua (Indonesian province)|Papua]] |speakers=100 |date=1987 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[East Geelvink Bay languages|East Geelvink Bay]]? |fam2= |iso3=srt |glotto=saur1251 |glottorefname=Sauri }} '''Sauri''' is a [[Papuan language]] of the [[Indonesia]]n province of [[Papua (province)|Papua]], on the eastern shore of [[Cenderawasih Bay]].
Sauri is lexically similar to the [[East Geelvink Bay languages]] and presumably belongs in that family, but is too poorly attested to be sure.
